Case 1:20-cr-00330-PAE Document 765 Filed 08/10/22 Page 87 of 95 2825 LCIAMAX2ps
1 MR. EVERDELL: Carolyn only, and it would say "sex trafficking of."
2
3 THE COURT: "An individual."
4 MR. EVERDELL: "Under the age of 18."
5 MR. ROHRBACH: That's fine, your Honor.
6 THE COURT: Taking out "a minor," adding "an individual under the age of 18," and then adding "only" after "Carolyn."
7
8 MR. EVERDELL: Correct, your Honor.
9
10 THE COURT: OK.
11 MR. EVERDELL: Moving back to Count Five, it's a little cumbersome, I understand, the way the language is. But it would say "sex trafficking conspiracy of individuals under the age of 18."
12
13
14
15 THE COURT: OK. Mr. Rohrbach.
16 MR. ROHRBACH: We think it's a little unclear to say "conspiracy to commit sex trafficking of individuals under the age of 18"?
17
18
19 MR. EVERDELL: That's fine.
20 THE COURT: So we'll change Count Five to "conspiracy to commit sex" -- how do you want to say it?
21
22 MR. EVERDELL: "conspiracy to commit sex trafficking of individuals under the age of 18."
23
24 THE COURT: 17.
25 MR. ROHRBACH: 18 for this.
SOUTHERN DISTRICT REPORTERS, P.C. (212) 805-0300
DOJ-OGR-00014391
